&quot;Miller Reese Hutchison (1876–1944) was an American electrical engineer and inventor. He developed some of the first portable electric devices, such as a vehicle horn and a hearing aid.&quot;
<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miller_Reese_Hutchison" rel="nofollow">en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miller_Reese_Hutchison</a>

In January 1916 (date on sticker: 1/25/16), he was involved in a trial about the explosion on board of a submarine, see <a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn83030272/1916-01-21/ed-1/seq-16/" rel="nofollow">The sun., January 21, 1916, Page 16</a>, column 5.
